# Defense in depth: ignore EVERYTHING in this directory by default, so a
# plaintext secret (e.g. an accidental `sops -d > secrets/plain.env`) or a
# stray age key can never be committed. Only the explicitly-listed files
# below — the ENCRYPTED secrets and the helpers — are tracked.
#
# This negation also overrides the repo-root `*.env` rule for the encrypted
# file (deeper .gitignore wins), so secrets.sops.env stays committable.
*
!.gitignore
!README.md
!with-secrets.sh
!secrets.sops.env
